<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://movieweb.com/movie/id4/ind2s.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
The visitors arrive!<br>
<br>
The question is finally answered -- is there anyone else out there? Well, yes...and, yes, they are technologically superior to us. No, they don't look like us, theyÅfre not cute, and they're not friendly like the visitors in the afore-mentioned film that admonished us all to just get along. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://movieweb.com/movie/id4/cods.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
They're going to exterminate us. That blows the common starry-eyed  speculation (at least for this story) that technologically advanced civilizations &quot;study war no more&quot;. This time there's a nowhere-near-human looking race of ET's in huge craft, entering our airspace all around the globe, preparing to finish off humanity and strip mine Earth's resources while a mother ship hovers above.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://movieweb.com/movie/id4/cocs.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
